---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Nostaliga — the photos behind the songs you loved"
  path="/"
>
  <section class="pt-16 pb-24">
    <p class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Coming soon to iPhone
    </p>
    <h1
      class="text-5xl leading-tight sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl"
      style="font-family: var(--font-display);"
    >
      A song you loved still knows where you were.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Play a track you were once obsessed with and Nostaliga resurfaces the
      photos you took back then — matched to your own listening history,
      privately, right on your device.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a
        href="mailto:dinakartumu@gmail.com?subject=Nostaliga%20TestFlight"
        class="rounded-full bg-[color:var(--color-accent)] px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[color:var(--color-bg)] hover:no-underline hover:brightness-110"
      >
        Request TestFlight access
      </a>
      <a
        href="/privacy"
        class="rounded-full border border-white/15 px-6 py-3 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-ink)] hover:no-underline hover:border-white/30"
      >
        How your data is handled
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-white/5 py-20">
    <p class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Why I built it
    </p>
    <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-6 text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      <p>
        I have a song — <em class="not-italic text-[color:var(--color-accent)]"
          >Aalaporaan Thamizhan</em
        > — that I played on every long ride around the Bay Area. I can't hear it
        now without those rides coming straight back: the road, the light, who I
        was then.
      </p>
      <p>
        Coldplay's <em class="not-italic text-[color:var(--color-accent)]"
          >Magic</em
        > does the same thing. It drops me into a trip to Boston, and the days I
        spent there with my uncle and cousin.
      </p>
      <p>
        Those memories never left — the song was the key, I just had no way to
        open the door. So I built Nostaliga. It notices what you're playing,
        looks back at when you used to play it on repeat, and brings the photos
        from that time back to the surface.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p
      class="mt-8 text-[color:var(--color-ink)]"
      style="font-family: var(--font-display);"
    >
      — Dinakar, founder
    </p>

    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-10 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <figure>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <img
            src="/story/bayarea-1.jpg"
            alt="Nostaliga showing Aalaporaan Thamizhan with 33 plays above a 2017 timeline"
            width="461"
            height="1000"
            loading="lazy"
            class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
          />
          <img
            src="/story/bayarea-2.jpg"
            alt="The photos resurfaced from the time Aalaporaan Thamizhan was on repeat"
            width="461"
            height="1000"
            loading="lazy"
            class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
          />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="mt-4 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
          <span class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">Aalaporaan Thamizhan</span>
          — Bay Area rides, 2017
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <img
            src="/story/boston-1.jpg"
            alt="Nostaliga showing Magic by Coldplay with 101 plays above a 2014 timeline"
            width="461"
            height="1000"
            loading="lazy"
            class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
          />
          <img
            src="/story/boston-2.jpg"
            alt="The photos resurfaced from the time Magic by Coldplay was on repeat"
            width="461"
            height="1000"
            loading="lazy"
            class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
          />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="mt-4 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
          <span class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">Magic</span>
          — Coldplay, 2014
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure>
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <img
            src="/story/newyork-1.jpg"
            alt="Nostaliga showing Malargal Kaettaen with 164 plays above a 2015 New York timeline"
            width="479"
            height="1000"
            loading="lazy"
            class="w-1/2 rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
          />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="mt-4 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
          <span class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">Malargal Kaettaen</span>
          — New York, 2015
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-white/5 py-20">
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Brings your memory together from everywhere you already are.
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl">Music</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
          Apple Music, Spotify, and Last.fm — every track you've listened to,
          when, and where.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl">Health</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
          Workouts from HealthKit alongside the soundtrack you had on.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl">Places</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
          Swarm check-ins and Strava routes remember the venues and paths each
          moment took.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl">Photos & words</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
          On-device photo matching and your Twitter archive round out what you
          actually saw and said.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-white/5 py-20">
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Private by design.
    </h2>
    <ul class="mt-8 space-y-3 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      <li>
        <span class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">On-device matching.</span>
        Photos, music, and health data are correlated locally — never uploaded.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">Keychain-only tokens.</span>
        Every third-party OAuth token stays in the iOS Keychain on your device.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">No tracking.</span>
        No analytics SDKs, no advertising identifier, no third-party trackers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">You're in control.</span>
        Disconnect any service or delete its imported history anytime in
        Settings → Integrations.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
